caption: The Effort sculpture is situated in the northwest corner of the Luxembourg Gardens. It is the work of Pierre Roche (1896). What you see is a male figure supposedly representing one of the twelve labours of Hercules. Originally intended to be part of a large fountain, The Effort instead found its way into the Gardens nuzzled up against trees and shrubs where you find it today. Worth a look-see if passing by and interested in sculptures.
In a corner of the large gardens, is a hidden in the shrubs a laying  bronze sculpture, depicting hercules, diverting the course of a river.
Pretty Sculpture nicely integrated into the decor.
